(thirdQuint)Fibroscan Predicts Complications After Hepatectomy.

 A prospective cohort study on consecutive patients scheduled for hepatectomy was planned.

 Fibroscan was performed during the preoperative workup.

 Accuracy of the liver stiffness and steatosis measured by Fibroscan in predicting the presence of cirrhosis, of steatosis, and the development of postoperative complications was assessed by ROC curve, and multivariate analysis.

